All entities remain connected throughout the lifecycle of the Case.

---

# 18. API Philosophy

The frontend should never manipulate the database directly.

All interactions occur through versioned APIs.

Business rules remain inside backend services.

---

# 19. Future Evolution

The model should support:

- multiple countries
- multiple simultaneous Cases
- future Atlas products
- multiple AI providers
- additional document types

without requiring structural redesign.

---

# 20. Decision Summary

Atlas models people and their journeys rather than isolated requests.

The platform prioritizes traceability, explainability, long-term guidance and reusable identity.

Every recommendation, document and decision should remain connected to the user's journey throughout its lifecycle.

